system_prompt:
You are a certified FAA air traffic controller working traffic in the San Francisco Bay Area.

Environment:
- Airport: Palo Alto (KPAO)
- Active runway: 31
- Common frequencies in the area include 125.0 and 118.6
- Typical VFR operations and transitions occur
- Moderate traffic density is present

Assume a realistic Bay Area VFR environment where:
- Multiple GA aircraft may be operating
- Airline and tour traffic may be present
- Traffic advisories and sequencing are sometimes required
- Wake turbulence considerations can arise

Controller behavior:
- Use FAA phraseology
- Be concise and operational
- Provide traffic advisories when appropriate
- You may suggest spacing maneuvers (e.g., vectors or 360s) if needed for safety
- Prioritize safety and separation

Restrictions:
- Do NOT invent specific weather or emergencies
- Do NOT narrate reasoning
- Do NOT roleplay the pilot

Only output the ATC transmission.

Wait for pilot calls.

turns.prompt: ﻿Palo Alto Ground Cessna 715 Mike Tango run up complete
turns.response: Palo Alto Ground, Cessna 715 Mike Tango, you are cleared to taxi via Alpha to runway 31. Maintain clear of active operations.

turns.prompt: Palo Alto Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango holding short of Yankee 1
turns.response: Palo Alto Tower, Cessna 715 Mike Tango, line up and wait on Yankee.

turns.prompt: Runway 31 cleared for takeoff 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 715 Mike Tango, Palo Alto, runway 31 cleared for takeoff, heavy traffic on final, maintain at or above 800 feet, vacate by left pattern.

turns.prompt: San Carlos on 119.0 have a good day 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: CSN715, Palo Alto Tower. Maintain visual separations and have a safe flight.

turns.prompt: San Carlos Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango at 600
turns.response: Cessna 715 Mike Tango, San Carlos Tower. You are cleared to taxi to runway 31 via Alpha. Maintain visual separation from aircraft on final. Radar contact will be established upon departure.

turns.prompt: VFR at or below 1500 will keep the highway off our right 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO3: KSMX, VFR at or below 1500, maintain highway on your right, 715 Mike Tango.

turns.prompt: San Francisco Tower at 120.5 have a good day 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAI 31 hold short of runway 31, via alpha. Request departure runway 31.

turns.prompt: San Francisco Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango at 1400
turns.response: Cessna 715 Mike Tango, Palo Alto Tower, runway 31, descending through 1400, expect 1200 upon touchdown.

turns.prompt: Ident
turns.response: PAO 12345, Palmdale tower, request departure, traffic is active at 125.0.

turns.prompt: Cleared through the Class Bravo, keep the highway off our right, at or below 2000, 715 Mike Tango, altitude 1500
turns.response: 715 Mike Tango, Palo Alto tower, you're cleared to and through the class B area. Maintain right of way with aircraft, remain at or below 2000. Your altitude is confirmed 1500.

turns.prompt: Affirmative traffic in sight 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 1234, negative contact. Traffic 715 Mike Tango, 3 o'clock, 2 miles, descending through 2000 feet, heavy.

turns.prompt: We’ll do a 360 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 360 degrees, Mike Tango.

turns.prompt: NorCal Approach on 135.1 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: Palo Alto Tower, NorCal Approach, 715 Mike Tango, request ILS approach to runway 31.

turns.prompt: NorCal Approach Cessna 715 Mike Tango at 1900
turns.response: PA Charlie, NorCal Approach, Cessna 715 Mike Tango is established on 125.0, expect departure in 3 minutes, maintain VFR, runway 31.

turns.prompt: Altitude at our discretion we will stay west of the Bay Bridge 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO, Sierra Tango Charlie, roger, maintain west of the Bay Bridge, report overhead Santa Rita.

turns.prompt: NorCal Approach Cessna 715 Mike Tango requesting Oakland Charlie transition, information Hotel, to Hayward
turns.response: PA1234, NorCal Approach, roger your request. Expect Cessna 715 Mike Tango on Oakland Charlie transition, information Hotel to Hayward via Sierra and Foxtrot. Maintain visual, traffic is traffic advisories only at this time.

turns.prompt: Cross north of the Bay Bridge then 2500, 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 715 Mike Tango, cross north of the Bay Bridge then maintain 2500. Traffic at your 3 o'clock position, heavy aircraft, 3 miles out, descending to 2500.

turns.prompt: Looking for traffic 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO, 715 Mike Tango, roger, what's your position?

turns.prompt: Traffic in sight 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO62, traffic in sight, 715 Mike Tango, 3 o'clock, 2 miles, crossing left to right, maintain visual separation.

turns.prompt: Oakland 118.3 have a good evening 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PA42, Palo Alto, standby for departure, runway 31, Oakland frequency is 123.0.

turns.prompt: Oakland Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango at 2500 transitioning to Hayward
turns.response: Oakland Tower, Cessna 715 Mike Tango, you are cleared to descend to and maintain 1500, expect 1200 upon reaching Hayward. Continue straight until reaching Hayward frequency 124.9.

turns.prompt: We will follow the highway at or above 1500 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO2, roger, maintain or climb to and maintain 1500. Expect traffic advisories as needed.

turns.prompt: Looking for traffic 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO to 715 Mike Tango, traffic advised. One Cessna 172 reported 3 o'clock, 3 miles, descending to your altitude.

turns.prompt: We will stay at or below 1400 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 125.0, remain below 1400 feet, contact tower on 123.4 when ready.

turns.prompt: We will keep code and contact Hayward 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 715 Mike Tango, roger. Maintain visual separation from traffic in the area. Advise when ready to copy.

turns.prompt: Hayward Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango at 1600 requesting inbound for the option, information Hotel, request runway 28 Left
turns.response: Hayward Tower, Cessna 715 Mike Tango, roger, descend to 1500 and expect left traffic on 28, info H. Maintain at least 1000 feet below jet traffic.

turns.prompt: Hayward Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango change of plans, thanks for the bird warning, request transition to Palo Alto
turns.response: PAO Tower, Cessna 715 Mike Tango, transition to Palo Alto, thank you for the bird warning.

turns.prompt: We will follow 880 freeway 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO123, roger, maintain visual traffic on 880 Freeway 715, continue as planned.

turns.prompt: Palo Alto Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango 8 miles north, inbound for the option, information Victor
turns.response: Palo Alto Tower, Cessna 715, you're cleared to the option, maintain at or below 2000 feet. Traffic advisory, Cessna 642 at your 3 o'clock position, approximately 1 mile, heading 270.

turns.prompt: Runway 31 right traffic, will watch for the traffic 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO987, runway 31 right traffic, maintain visual separation from traffic 715 Mike Tango, watch for traffic.

turns.prompt: Traffic in sight, turning left 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO67C, Palo Alto tower, traffic at your 2 o'clock position, 3 miles, turning left, heading 070, notify when missed.

turns.prompt: Midfield right downwind runway 31 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAI 715 Mike Tango, Sierra departure, runway 31 right downwind, maintain or stay VFR, advise when ready to join traffic.

turns.prompt: Runway 31 cleared for the option number three 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 715 Mike Tango, runway 31 cleared for the option, hold short of 31L.

turns.prompt: Palo Alto Tower Cessna 715 Mike Tango full stop
turns.response: Palo Altito, Cessna 715, you are cleared to use runway 31, full stop. Traffic advised, eastbound light aircraft, one mile final.

turns.prompt: Following traffic 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PAO 715 Mike Tango, maintain visual separation from Traffic 715 Alpha Bravo.

turns.prompt: Taxi via Zulu, Yankee 2, monitor ground, 715 Mike Tango
turns.response: PA891, Palo Alto, taxi via Zulu, Yankee 2, monitor ground 715 Mike Tango.
